<div class="post-date">Jan 11</div>
<h2><a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?id=836" title="When I was a kid,"> When I was a kid,</a></h2>

<div class="entry">


     

  	<p>When I was a kid, this was my favorite series of mysteries.</p>

	<p>I found one at a bookstore once and have been collecting them since. They&#8217;re a lot of fun, good solid fluff reading now, but definitely a good read for 3-5 graders.</p>

	<p>The series features three California boys who together formed an investigation agency that tackles the craziest mysteries featuring things from singing serpents and crooked cats to screaming clocks and dancing devils.</p>

	<p>The mysteries are puzzles, but fair&#8212;a sharp kid can solve them along with first investigator Jupiter Jones.</p>

	<p>I love their business card. It features three question marks ??? &#8220;The question mark is the universal symbol of something unknown. We are prepared to solve any puzzle, riddle, mystery, enigma, or conundrum which may be brought to us,&#8221; Jupiter Jones explains in the first book.</p>

	<p>As a reference assistant and someone who loves to encourage kids to read, these guys are my heroes.</p>



 
<div class="line"></div>

<div class="smallcat">Posted in <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?c=Culture">Culture</a></div>
<div class="smalluser"> by <a https://yarnetsky.github.io/ontheriversedge/index.html?author=E.G.+Yarnetsky">E.G. Yarnetsky</a></div>
